CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 10, 1962, pg. 24 reads: "Most Valuable - Frank Robinson, star slugger with the Cincinnati Reds and the "Most Valuable Player" in National League in 1961, was an honored guest in Pittsburgh, last Sunday, for the Dapper Dan banquet. Robinson, a big hit at the affair, is shown in conversation with one of his fans."
TitMainTitle: Cincinnati Reds baseball player Frank Robinson shaking hands with unknown man, posed in Kings Garden, Hilton Hotel for Dapper Dan banquet
